    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nLet's take this one step at a time! Click the arrow to expand the step when you're ready.\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">1. Add a <code>Painter</code> parameter to the functions</span>]\r\n\r\nLook at the `take_four_paint()` and `paint_then_move()` functions near the top of the code.\r\n\r\nEach function is missing a parameter. Add `this_painter` inside the parentheses so your functions know which `Painter` to use.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">2. Update both functions to use the parameter</span>]\r\n\r\nInside the functions, replace `mika` and `luca` with `this_painter`.\r\n\r\nThis allows your functions to work with any `Painter` object.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">3. Call the functions with <code>mika</code> as the argument</span>]\r\n\r\nScroll through the code and look for the `TODO`s where the functions should be used with `mika`.\r\n\r\nReplace the repeated lines where `mika` takes paint or paints and moves with calls to: `take_four_paint(mika)` and `paint_then_move(mika)`.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">4. Call the functions with <code>luca</code> as the argument</span>]\r\n\r\nNow scroll down and look for the `TODO`s where `luca` is working.\r\n\r\nReplace the lines where `luca` takes paint with a call to `take_four_paint(luca)`. Then update the call to `paint_then_move()` so that it passes in `luca`.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/a7d5e637494450015640b88552683d1c-choiceD.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo make your function flexible, use a parameter like `this_painter` so the function works with any `Painter` you choose.\r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef paint_line(this_painter):\r\n  this_painter.take_paint()\r\n  this_painter.paint(\"white\")\r\n  this_painter.move()\r\n\r\npaint_line(south_side_painter)\r\n```",
